cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.DS, cs.SE, cs.RO 

This paper focuses on a classification problem that involves acquiring information about a sample for a cost, which is a common problem in machine learning and artificial intelligence. The paper proposes a solution using deep reinforcement learning, which falls under the categories of cs.LG (Machine Learning), cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence), and cs.RO (Robotics). Additionally, the paper deals with missing features in the training dataset, which falls under the category of cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms). Finally, the paper discusses the problem in the context of software engineering, which falls under the category of cs.SE (Software Engineering).
